A student wants to check whether a grade is between 60 and 100 (inclusive). Their code always prints "pass" even for a grade of 200. What is the bug?

```cpp
#include <iostream>
int main()
{
    int grade = 200;
    if (60 <= grade <= 100)
        std::cout << "pass\n";
    else
        std::cout << "fail\n";
    return 0;
}
```
